# ─── English Quest — environment variables ─────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to `.env.local` for local development.
# The demo login works with NO configuration at all.

# Public Google OAuth Client ID for client-side "Sign in with Google"
# (Google Identity Services). This value is PUBLIC and safe to commit / bake
# into the static build — there is no client secret in this flow.
#
# Create one at https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
#   → Create credentials → OAuth client ID → Web application
#
# Add EXACTLY these "Authorized JavaScript origins" (scheme + host, no path —
# the /english-quest base path is NOT part of the origin):
#   http://localhost:3000          ← local dev
#   https://am-piyus.github.io     ← production (GitHub Pages)
# A missing/mismatched origin is the #1 cause of a button that renders but does
# nothing. No redirect URIs are needed (GIS returns the token in-page).
#
# The app uses the FedCM flow, so sign-in keeps working as browsers phase out
# third-party cookies. The ID is validated client-side only; server-side token
# verification is a V0.2 item (needs a backend — can't run on static Pages).
#
# For GitHub Pages, set this as a repository *variable* named
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID (Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → Variables).
# It must end with `.apps.googleusercontent.com`.
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
